tool.name: ProcessMultiNet

param.name: in_network_geometry_fc
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® network geometry feature class.

param.name: in_maneuvers_geometry_fc
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® maneuvers geometry feature class.

param.name: in_maneuver_path_index_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® manuever path index table.

param.name: in_sign_information_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® sign information table.

param.name: in_sign_path_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® sign path table.

param.name: in_restrictions_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® restrictions table.

param.name: output_folder
param.dialogReference: The folder where the output geodatabase containing the new network dataset will be created.

param.name: output_geodatabase_name
param.dialogReference: The name for the output geodatabase that will be created.

param.name: unit_type
param.dialogReference: Whether the network dataset's attributes should use imperial or metric units. Valid options include "Imperial" and "Metric".

param.name: build_network
param.dialogReference: Boolean indicating whether to build the output network dataset immediately after creating it. After this tool creates the network dataset, if you intend to make further changes to it prior to performing any analysis, you may want to set this parameter to false so that the network dataset isn't built just yet. Once you've completed making the additional changes, then you can run the Build Network tool to build the network dataset.

param.name: include_historical_traffic
param.dialogReference: Boolean indicating whether to include historical traffic data in the network dataset.

param.name: in_network_profile_link_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® network profile link table. This table is required if Include historical traffic is true.

param.name: in_historical_speed_profiles_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® historical speed profiles table. This table is required if Include historical traffic is true.

param.name: in_rds_tmc_info_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® RDS-TMC information table. This table is optional and only used if Include historical traffic is true.

param.name: include_multinet_logistics_restriction_data
param.dialogReference: Boolean indicating whether to include extended logistics restrictions in the network dataset.

param.name: in_logistics_restrictions_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® logistics restrictions table. This table is required if Include MultiNet Logistics restriction data is true.

param.name: in_logistics_vehicle_characteristics_table
param.dialogReference: The TomTom® MultiNet® logistics vehicle characteristics table. This table is required if Include MultiNet Logistics restriction data is true.

param.name: time_zone_type
param.expression: {None | Single time zone | Use time zone table}
param.dialogReference:
How to handle time zones in the network dataset.

  • "None": Do not include a time zone attribute in the network dataset.

  • "Single time zone": A time zone attribute is created, and all features in the network dataset are assigned to the time zone specified in the Time Zone Name parameter.

  • "Use time zone table": A time zone attribute is created, and features in the network dataset are assigned to time zones according to an input table specified in the Input Time Zone Table parameter.

param.name: time_zone_name
param.dialogReference: If Time Zone Type is "Single time zone", this parameter specifies the name of the time zone. This parameter is ignored for other values of Time Zone Type.

param.name: in_time_zone_table
param.dialogReference: If Time Zone Type is "Use time zone table", this parameter specifies the table defining the time zones. This parameter is ignored for other values of Time Zone Type.

param.name: in_ft_time_zone_field_name
param.displayname: Input FT Time Zone ID Field Name
param.dialogReference: If Time Zone Type is "Use time zone table", this parameter specifies the field in the Input Network Geometry (NW) Feature Class defining the feature's time zone in the feature's From-To direction (in the direction of digitization). This parameter is ignored for other values of Time Zone Type.

param.name: in_tf_time_zone_field_name
param.displayname: Input TF Time Zone ID Field Name
param.dialogReference: If Time Zone Type is "Use time zone table", this parameter specifies the field in the Input Network Geometry (NW) Feature Class defining the feature's time zone in the feature's To-From direction (against the direction of digitization). This parameter is ignored for other values of Time Zone Type.

tool.summary: Process TomTom® MultiNet® data for a network dataset
